# GitOps Project Structure Guide

This is a GitOps infrastructure management project using ArgoCD and Kustomize. The main structure follows:

## Bootstrap Layer
- [bootstrap/base/](mdc:bootstrap/base/) - Base bootstrap configuration with root ArgoCD Application
- [bootstrap/overlays/](mdc:bootstrap/overlays/) - Environment-specific bootstrap overlays (e.g., hetzner-k8s)

## Cluster Configuration
- [clusters/base/](mdc:clusters/base/) - Base cluster configuration manifests
- [clusters/overlays/](mdc:clusters/overlays/) - Environment-specific cluster overlays

## Key Files
- [bootstrap/base/root-application.yaml](mdc:bootstrap/base/root-application.yaml) - Root ArgoCD Application that bootstraps everything
- [bootstrap/base/kustomization.yaml](mdc:bootstrap/base/kustomization.yaml) - Base kustomization including root application
- [bootstrap/overlays/hetzner-k8s/kustomization.yaml](mdc:bootstrap/overlays/hetzner-k8s/kustomization.yaml) - Hetzner-specific overlay configuration

## Workflow
1. Bootstrap base creates root Application with placeholder values
2. Overlays patch the base to configure environment-specific settings
3. Root Application deploys cluster configurations from clusters/overlays/
4. Cluster configs then manage tenant applications

Always check the overlay structure when making changes - base configurations are patched by overlays for environment-specific customization.
